1
00:00:01,085 --> 00:00:02,544
[ mouse squeaks ]

2
00:00:02,628 --> 00:00:04,129
[ penguins wenk ]

3
00:00:06,215 --> 00:00:07,299
[ all cheering ]

4
00:00:10,386 --> 00:00:11,512
[ screeches ]

5
00:00:13,389 --> 00:00:14,473
D> Adventure Time )

6
00:00:14,556 --> 00:00:16,475
» Come on, grab your friends »

7
00:00:16,558 --> 00:00:18,602
» We'll go to very distant lands J

8
00:00:18,686 --> 00:00:20,729
» With Jake the Dog
and Finn the Human »

9
00:00:20,813 --> 00:00:22,356
D The fun will never end >

10
00:00:22,439 --> 00:00:24,566
D It's Adventure Time »

11
00:00:34,201 --> 00:00:35,911
Slam!

12
00:00:35,994 --> 00:00:37,705
[ both chuckling ]

13
00:00:39,331 --> 00:00:40,666
"Hey, | was trying
to read that!"

14
00:00:40,749 --> 00:00:43,293
"That book is above
your level."

15
00:00:43,377 --> 00:00:45,087
"What business are
you into?"

16
00:00:45,170 --> 00:00:46,839
"None of your
business!"

17
00:00:46,922 --> 00:00:48,632
"Talk about it
over lunch?"

18
00:00:48,716 --> 00:00:51,510
"Heh, if you're buying."

19
00:00:57,558 --> 00:00:59,810
- IIHey!II
- IIHey!II

20
00:00:59,893 --> 00:01:02,646
BOTH:
"Fight!"

21
00:01:02,730 --> 00:01:04,732
[ both grunting ]

22
00:01:04,815 --> 00:01:06,859
Aah! It's terrible!

23
00:01:06,942 --> 00:01:08,527
TOGETHER:
Lumpy Space Princess?!

24
00:01:08,610 --> 00:01:09,945
What's wrong?

25
00:01:10,028 --> 00:01:12,531
You guys, somebody stole
something from me --

26
00:01:12,614 --> 00:01:15,033
something | can't live
without!

27
00:01:15,117 --> 00:01:16,785
I'll get something
to calm her down.

28
00:01:16,869 --> 00:01:18,412
I've been robbed!

29
00:01:18,495 --> 00:01:20,080
PB:
Out of the way!

30
00:01:20,164 --> 00:01:22,207
Aaaaah!

31
00:01:22,291 --> 00:01:23,500
[ hysterical gibberish ]

32
00:01:23,584 --> 00:01:25,377
| need help!
Can you guys hold her down?

33
00:01:25,461 --> 00:01:26,670
You have to do something!

34
00:01:26,754 --> 00:01:28,380
I've been -- unh! --

35
00:01:28,464 --> 00:01:31,800
r-o-o-o-obb-e-e-d.

36
00:01:31,884 --> 00:01:33,177
Oh.

37
00:01:33,260 --> 00:01:35,387
[ groggy gibberish ]

38
00:01:35,471 --> 00:01:36,513
Oops.

39
00:01:36,597 --> 00:01:38,056
LSP, who robbed you?

40
00:01:38,140 --> 00:01:39,975
It... was...

41
00:01:40,058 --> 00:01:42,811
Puh -- Pete...
Pete...

42
00:01:42,895 --> 00:01:45,397
Sa -- Sass -- as --

43
00:01:45,481 --> 00:01:47,691
[ gibberish ]

44
00:01:47,775 --> 00:01:48,942
Oh, uh...

45
00:01:49,026 --> 00:01:49,902
[ body thuds ]

46
00:01:49,985 --> 00:01:52,696
| think | gave her
too much.

47
00:01:52,780 --> 00:01:54,698
Jake, a crime has
been committed.

48
00:01:54,782 --> 00:01:56,700
We must find the criminal...
- We must.

49
00:01:56,784 --> 00:01:58,327
...and retrieve
whatever it is

50
00:01:58,410 --> 00:01:59,953
that was stolen from
Lumpy Space Princess!

51
00:02:00,037 --> 00:02:01,288
Stolen.

52
00:02:01,371 --> 00:02:04,124
But all we have to go on
is part of a name --

53
00:02:04,208 --> 00:02:05,501
Pete something.

54
00:02:05,584 --> 00:02:06,835
Need more clues!

55
00:02:06,919 --> 00:02:08,796
Hold me!

56
00:02:10,672 --> 00:02:12,883
Clues, clues,
clues...

57
00:02:12,966 --> 00:02:15,093
[ groaning ]

58
00:02:15,177 --> 00:02:17,262
What's that?
| can't see it.

59
00:02:17,346 --> 00:02:19,264
Oop. Sorry.
Ahh.

60
00:02:19,348 --> 00:02:20,974
There's something in
her hand!

61
00:02:21,058 --> 00:02:22,226
A key!

62
00:02:22,309 --> 00:02:24,853
A key to... what?

63
00:02:24,937 --> 00:02:26,438
"3_0_3 . n

64
00:02:26,522 --> 00:02:27,606
Hmm.

65
00:02:27,689 --> 00:02:30,317
Ooh! Turn it around.

66
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,318
Ah!

67
00:02:31,401 --> 00:02:34,279
Looks like we got
our first lead.

68
00:02:39,952 --> 00:02:41,912
[ imitates gun cocking ]

69
00:02:41,995 --> 00:02:44,206
Unh!

70
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:48,377
Hmm.
Found anything yet, Jake?

71
00:02:48,460 --> 00:02:50,629
| got some bags
and...

72
00:02:50,712 --> 00:02:51,630
Wait!

73
00:02:51,713 --> 00:02:53,465
More bags.

74
00:02:53,549 --> 00:02:55,551
But no leads
on Pete something.

75
00:02:55,634 --> 00:02:57,010
Same here.

76
00:02:57,094 --> 00:02:59,930
Beemo, start marking
evidence.

77
00:03:08,313 --> 00:03:10,232
Hmm.

78
00:03:12,901 --> 00:03:15,195
Hmm.

79
00:03:15,279 --> 00:03:16,780
Hmmm.

80
00:03:18,198 --> 00:03:20,242
Dude, check this.

81
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:22,411
Is this blood?

82
00:03:22,494 --> 00:03:24,496
Yeah, man,
that's definitely blood.

83
00:03:24,580 --> 00:03:25,664
Hmm.

84
00:03:25,747 --> 00:03:27,833
LSP's injuries were
100% emotional.

85
00:03:27,916 --> 00:03:30,502
So it has to belong to
Pete Sa-something.

86
00:03:30,586 --> 00:03:33,297
Beemo, take a sample and do
a full blood analysis.

87
00:03:33,380 --> 00:03:34,798
The "woiks."

88
00:03:34,882 --> 00:03:37,134
Hey, if that guy cut himself
during the robbery,

89
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:39,011
he might have gone
somewhere to buy

90
00:03:39,094 --> 00:03:40,679
a mini adhesive bandage.

91
00:03:40,762 --> 00:03:42,389
There's a drug store
across the street.

92
00:03:42,472 --> 00:03:44,141
Let's roll!

93
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:46,018
Whoa!

94
00:03:48,061 --> 00:03:49,980
JAKE:
Vroom!

95
00:03:50,063 --> 00:03:51,690
[ imitates brakes squealing,
car idling ]

96
00:03:51,773 --> 00:03:54,401
And if the oozing persists,
just come back...

97
00:03:54,484 --> 00:03:56,862
and I'll give you something
a little stronger.

98
00:03:56,945 --> 00:03:59,156
I'm Finn.
This is my partner Jake.

99
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:01,491
Hello, citizen, had anyone
in here looking to buy

100
00:04:01,575 --> 00:04:03,619
some mini adhesive bandages today?

101
00:04:03,702 --> 00:04:05,579
A lot of people come through
my store, gentlemen.

102
00:04:05,662 --> 00:04:08,040
You can't seriously think
I'd be able to remember

103
00:04:08,123 --> 00:04:10,125
any one particular customer
among the countless others

104
00:04:10,208 --> 00:04:13,128
| see on a daily basis
now, can you?

105
00:04:13,211 --> 00:04:15,464
| guess not.

106
00:04:15,547 --> 00:04:16,965
Fair do's.
Come on, Jake --

107
00:04:17,049 --> 00:04:17,966
Wait!

108
00:04:18,050 --> 00:04:19,468
Now that you mention it,

109
00:04:19,551 --> 00:04:21,303
there was this one guy
in here earlier.

110
00:04:21,386 --> 00:04:23,847
Real suspicious type.
Had a nose bleed.

111
00:04:23,931 --> 00:04:25,641
Said it was the first one
he'd had in years.

112
00:04:25,724 --> 00:04:27,643
Used to get them all the time
as a kid, he said.

113
00:04:27,726 --> 00:04:29,853
Could never remember if he was
supposed to pinch his nose

114
00:04:29,937 --> 00:04:31,229
and hold his head back

115
00:04:31,313 --> 00:04:33,273
or pinch his nose and hold
his head forward.

116
00:04:33,357 --> 00:04:35,275
Maybe it was a case
of being boxed

117
00:04:35,359 --> 00:04:37,069
on the nose
too many times --

118
00:04:37,152 --> 00:04:38,654
made the blood vessels
in his lower septum weak

119
00:04:38,737 --> 00:04:40,656
and vulnerable
to hemorrhaging.

120
00:04:40,739 --> 00:04:41,823
Anyway, his mammy always said

121
00:04:41,907 --> 00:04:44,368
it was because he couldn't keep
those picky little fingers

122
00:04:44,451 --> 00:04:46,203
out of his dirty little
nose holes.

123
00:04:46,286 --> 00:04:47,746
He didn't buy it, though.
He always thought --

124
00:04:47,829 --> 00:04:49,456
Ma'am, can you give us
a name?

125
00:04:49,539 --> 00:04:51,083
Mmmmm, nope.

126
00:04:51,166 --> 00:04:53,293
No, wait.
Yes, | can.

127
00:04:53,377 --> 00:04:55,379
Pete Sassafrass.

128
00:04:56,588 --> 00:04:57,881
Pete...

129
00:04:57,965 --> 00:05:00,717
Sa -- Sass -- as...

130
00:05:00,801 --> 00:05:02,594
Did you catch which
way he was going?

131
00:05:02,678 --> 00:05:05,222
Of course. He said he was
catching a train at 11:27,

132
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:07,391
Candy Kingdom station,
Platform 5.

133
00:05:07,474 --> 00:05:10,644
Heh. I'm sorry.
| wish | could remember more.

134
00:05:13,981 --> 00:05:15,774
See anyone who might
be our guy?

135
00:05:15,857 --> 00:05:16,984
[ sighs ]
Nope.

136
00:05:17,067 --> 00:05:19,277
Nobody suspicious here.

137
00:05:19,361 --> 00:05:23,615
Just a load of decent,
law-abiding folk.

138
00:05:23,699 --> 00:05:24,700
What the --

139
00:05:24,783 --> 00:05:26,910
Jake, what's with all the
turning into stuff today?

140
00:05:26,994 --> 00:05:28,912
| really like turning
into cop stuff.

141
00:05:28,996 --> 00:05:31,081
| literally can't stop
turning into cop stuff.

142
00:05:31,164 --> 00:05:32,290
PA ANNOUNCER:
Final boarding...

143
00:05:32,374 --> 00:05:34,292
Hey, there's
Platform 5.

144
00:05:34,376 --> 00:05:36,461
...service to
Peppermint Hills, Track 5.

145
00:05:36,545 --> 00:05:38,296
[ gasps ]
| see a nasty "tranch™!

146
00:05:38,380 --> 00:05:39,965
Let's book 'im, son.

147
00:05:40,048 --> 00:05:41,383
Hup! Sorry!

148
00:05:41,466 --> 00:05:42,801
Whoa!
Comin' through!

149
00:05:44,553 --> 00:05:45,637
Hup!
[ grunts ]

150
00:05:45,721 --> 00:05:47,097
Stop right there!

151
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:49,099
What's under that skeezy
trench coat, you --

152
00:05:49,182 --> 00:05:50,726
- Crook!
- [ both grunt ]

153
00:05:50,809 --> 00:05:53,061
Busted! For attempting
to board a train

154
00:05:53,145 --> 00:05:54,396
without a ticket.

155
00:05:54,479 --> 00:05:57,232
[ train horn blows ]

156
00:05:57,315 --> 00:05:58,817
Aw, guys,
he's getting away!

157
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:00,402
We're not criminals, man!

158
00:06:00,485 --> 00:06:01,945
We're working the beat,
just like you!

159
00:06:02,029 --> 00:06:03,155
Jimmy?

160
00:06:06,491 --> 00:06:08,410
Yep, checks out.
He tastes like police.

161
00:06:08,493 --> 00:06:09,953
Eh, sorry about that,
officers.

162
00:06:10,037 --> 00:06:12,497
It was an honest mistake.

163
00:06:12,581 --> 00:06:14,583
Ugh! We lost him.

164
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:17,085
JAKE:
Not yet we didn't.

165
00:06:18,545 --> 00:06:20,839
[ imitates siren wailing ]

166
00:06:23,091 --> 00:06:25,802
Unh! Too far ahead.
We'll never catch it!

167
00:06:25,886 --> 00:06:27,304
If we cut through the forest,

168
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:29,222
maybe we can head it off
at the pass.

169
00:06:29,306 --> 00:06:30,265
Sweet thinking!

170
00:06:30,348 --> 00:06:32,434
[ imitates tires screeching ]

171
00:06:32,517 --> 00:06:34,728
[ both scream ]

172
00:06:34,811 --> 00:06:36,563
Oh, deer!

173
00:06:39,232 --> 00:06:40,859
BOTH:
Yeah!

174
00:06:40,942 --> 00:06:42,319
[ grunts ]

175
00:06:45,864 --> 00:06:47,491
Are you
Pete Sassafrass?

176
00:06:47,574 --> 00:06:50,786
Wha?
... got a lot of names.

177
00:06:50,869 --> 00:06:52,788
Who's askin'?

178
00:06:52,871 --> 00:06:54,456
[ imitates gun cocking ]

179
00:06:54,539 --> 00:06:56,458
Give back what you stole
from LSP!

180
00:06:56,541 --> 00:06:58,460
Who? What's that?
An acronym or somethin'?

181
00:06:58,543 --> 00:06:59,711
Oofl

182
00:06:59,795 --> 00:07:00,796
Cuff him.

183
00:07:00,879 --> 00:07:02,297
[ grunts ]

184
00:07:02,380 --> 00:07:05,884
All right, | got this.
Oof!

185
00:07:05,967 --> 00:07:07,969
[ grunting ]

186
00:07:08,053 --> 00:07:09,805
You have the right
to remain --

187
00:07:09,888 --> 00:07:13,141
[ breathes deeply ]
Busted.

188
00:07:13,225 --> 00:07:15,185
All right, you listen,
flatfoot.

189
00:07:15,268 --> 00:07:17,395
There's been some kind of crazy
mistake here.

190
00:07:17,479 --> 00:07:19,022
| didn't do nothin'!

191
00:07:19,106 --> 00:07:21,608
Save it for
the Candy Judge, Pete.

192
00:07:21,691 --> 00:07:23,026
Look, you can drop
the act

193
00:07:23,110 --> 00:07:24,653
and cut the sass,
Sassafrass.

194
00:07:24,736 --> 00:07:26,905
We've got an eyewitness
and your blood

195
00:07:26,988 --> 00:07:29,074
at the scene of the crime.

196
00:07:29,157 --> 00:07:32,244
You do the crime,
you do the time, man.

197
00:07:32,327 --> 00:07:34,329
Roll the dice,
you pay the price.

198
00:07:34,412 --> 00:07:36,331
What dice?
Oh, you guys are donkers.

199
00:07:36,414 --> 00:07:39,626
Burgle our friend,
it's the end...

200
00:07:39,709 --> 00:07:41,837
for yo-0-0-0-0-u.

201
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:43,922
| want to see a lawyer.

202
00:07:44,005 --> 00:07:46,133
[ clears throat ]
I'll handle this, Pete.

203
00:07:46,216 --> 00:07:47,801
You're upsetting my client.

204
00:07:47,884 --> 00:07:49,511
Just look at that face.

205
00:07:49,594 --> 00:07:51,513
That constitutes harassment,
so give him some space.

206
00:07:51,596 --> 00:07:53,390
Don't worry, buddy.
I've got this case.

207
00:07:53,473 --> 00:08:02,774
[ both laugh ]

208
00:08:02,858 --> 00:08:05,694
"Welcome to the next 25 years
of your life!"

209
00:08:05,777 --> 00:08:08,363
[ sighs ]
We deserve doughnuts.

210
00:08:08,446 --> 00:08:09,781
Let's bowl.

211
00:08:09,865 --> 00:08:11,908
No, no, wait, please.

212
00:08:11,992 --> 00:08:14,703
You guys!

213
00:08:14,786 --> 00:08:16,580
"Guilty!"

214
00:08:19,499 --> 00:08:22,127
Man, we didn't just
crack that case...

215
00:08:22,210 --> 00:08:24,796
We crunched it.
Crumbled it.

216
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:27,549
We are awesome at
being cops.

217
00:08:27,632 --> 00:08:29,176
There's no question
about that.

218
00:08:29,259 --> 00:08:31,595
Ah, call me crazy,
but | was thinking...

219
00:08:31,678 --> 00:08:33,763
maybe we should actually
become detectives,

220
00:08:33,847 --> 00:08:36,224
like as a job!

221
00:08:36,308 --> 00:08:37,976
When we were out on the streets
back there,

222
00:08:38,059 --> 00:08:39,936
getting those leads,
busting that perp,

223
00:08:40,020 --> 00:08:42,230
it just felt so --
| don't know --

224
00:08:42,314 --> 00:08:43,315
right.

225
00:08:43,398 --> 00:08:45,650
| know, man.

226
00:08:45,734 --> 00:08:49,154
| actually totally do know
exactly what you mean.

227
00:08:50,155 --> 00:08:51,990
Ah. Dude.

228
00:08:52,073 --> 00:08:54,618
| told you, | have a
problem.

229
00:08:54,701 --> 00:08:56,828
| can't stop.

230
00:08:56,912 --> 00:08:59,247
- [ sighs ]
- Howdy, partner.

231
00:08:59,331 --> 00:09:00,624
Oh, hey, Beemo.
What's going on?

232
00:09:00,707 --> 00:09:02,375
I've finished processing
the blood sample,

233
00:09:02,459 --> 00:09:04,836
and | have the results.

234
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:07,297
- Nice.
- Yeah, good work, Beemo.

235
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:09,341
It's Pete Sassafrass's
blood, right?

236
00:09:09,424 --> 00:09:13,136
No, it doesn't belong to
anyone because it's not blood.

237
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:16,348
It's tomato sauce.

238
00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:18,808
Tomato sauce?

239
00:09:18,892 --> 00:09:20,268
Hmm.

240
00:09:20,352 --> 00:09:23,730
[ grunting ]

241
00:09:23,813 --> 00:09:25,023
Pete...

242
00:09:25,106 --> 00:09:27,943
Sa -- Sass -- as --

243
00:09:28,026 --> 00:09:29,611
Pete...sa --

244
00:09:29,694 --> 00:09:31,446
Oh, my mind!

245
00:09:31,529 --> 00:09:34,449
LSP wasn't trying to say
"Pete Sa-something."

246
00:09:34,532 --> 00:09:36,576
She was trying to say "pizza"
something!

247
00:09:36,660 --> 00:09:40,247
But how would pizza sauce
end up in a hotel room?

248
00:09:40,330 --> 00:09:42,749
Unless it was
delivered.

249
00:09:42,832 --> 00:09:44,584
[ both breathing heavily ]

250
00:09:44,668 --> 00:09:47,295
BOTH:
Pizza Sassy's!

251
00:09:47,379 --> 00:09:49,297
Where is the delivery
guy?!

252
00:09:49,381 --> 00:09:50,966
Oh, you mean Petey.

253
00:09:51,049 --> 00:09:54,302
He's out.
He's making deliveries.

254
00:09:54,386 --> 00:09:57,180
Or maybe he's out
tying up loose ends.

255
00:09:57,264 --> 00:09:59,349
[ gasps ]
LSP could be in dange-r-r-r-r!

256
00:09:59,432 --> 00:10:02,185
Dange-r-r-r-r!

257
00:10:02,269 --> 00:10:04,688
- Phone?
- Phone.

258
00:10:04,771 --> 00:10:06,523
[ panting ]

259
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:08,525
[ imitates phone dialing ]
Princess!

260
00:10:08,608 --> 00:10:11,194
Add some Banana Guards outside
of LSP's hospital room.

261
00:10:11,278 --> 00:10:12,529
Huh? Why?

262
00:10:12,612 --> 00:10:14,239
LSP could be in
danger!

263
00:10:14,322 --> 00:10:16,992
LSP woke up and
went back to her hotel room.

264
00:10:17,075 --> 00:10:19,119


265
